imself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Cochrane was born in 1365, in Renfrew, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Goseline de Cochrane, was 50 and his mother, Mary Francis de Bird, was 51. He had at least 1 son with Mary Lindsay. He died in Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1365–":"1365–Surnud","1344–Male":"1344–Surnud","1365–Male":"1365–Surnud","1365–1420":"1365–1420","1432–1484":"1432–1484","1315–1400":"1315–1400","1315":"1315","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1344":"1344","1365":"1365","25 September 1432":"25. september 1432","1420":"1420","1484":"1484","Cochrane, Renfrew, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrew, Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Fernois, Paisley, Renfrenshire Dist, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1365–":"1365–Kuollut","1344–Male":"1344–Kuollut","1365–Male":"1365–Kuollut","1365–1420":"1365–1420","1432–1484":"1432–1484","1315–1400":"1315–1400","1315":"1315","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1344":"1344","1365":"1365","25 September 1432":"25. syyskuuta 1432","1420":"1420","1484":"1484","Cochrane, Renfrew, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Renfrew, Renfrewshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fernois, Paisley, Renfrenshire Dist, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1365–":"1365–Décédé","1344–Male":"1344–Décédé","1365–Male":"1365–Décédé","1365–1420":"1365–1420","1432–1484":"1432–1484","1315–1400":"1315–1400","1315":"1